msgctxt "dn22:20.67"
msgid "4.5.4. Maggasaccaniddesa"
msgstr "4.5.4. The Path"

#. </h4><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs21"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc119"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:21.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṃ?"
msgstr ""
"And what is the noble truth of the practice that leads to the cessation of "
"suffering?"

msgctxt "dn22:21.2"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "dn22:21.3"
msgid ""
"sammādiṭṭhi sammāsaṅkappo sammāvācā sammākammanto sammāājīvo sammāvāyāmo "
"sammāsati sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.312"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc120"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:21.4"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sammādiṭṭhi?"
msgstr "And what is right view?"

msgctxt "dn22:21.5"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dukkhe ñāṇaṃ, dukkhasamudaye ñāṇaṃ, dukkhanirodhe ñāṇaṃ, "
"dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya ñāṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Knowing about suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of "
"suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering."

msgctxt "dn22:21.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammādiṭṭhi. (1)"
msgstr "This is called right view."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc121"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:21.7"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammāsaṅkappo?"
msgstr "And what is right thought?"

msgctxt "dn22:21.8"
msgid "Nekkhammasaṅkappo abyāpādasaṅkappo avihiṃsāsaṅkappo."
msgstr "Thoughts of renunciation, love, and kindness."

msgctxt "dn22:21.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāsaṅkappo. (2)"
msgstr "This is called right thought."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc122"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:21.10"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sammāvācā?"
msgstr "And what is right speech?"

#. VAR: veramaṇī → veramaṇi (mr)
msgctxt "dn22:21.11"
msgid ""
"Musāvādā veramaṇī pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī "
"samphappalāpā veramaṇī."
msgstr ""
"The refraining from lying, divisive speech, harsh speech, and talking "
"nonsense."

msgctxt "dn22:21.12"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāvācā. (3)"
msgstr "This is called right speech."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc123"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:21.13"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammākammanto?"
msgstr "And what is right action?"

msgctxt "dn22:21.14"
msgid "Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī adinnādānā veramaṇī kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī."
msgstr ""
"Refraining from killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct."

msgctxt "dn22:21.15"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammākammanto. (4)"
msgstr "This is called right action."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc124"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:21.16"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammāājīvo?"
msgstr "And what is right livelihood?"

msgctxt "dn22:21.17"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako micchāājīvaṃ pahāya sammāājīvena jīvitaṃ "
"kappeti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a noble disciple gives up wrong livelihood and earns a living by "
"right livelihood."

msgctxt "dn22:21.18"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāājīvo. (5)"
msgstr "This is called right livelihood."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.313"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc125"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:21.19"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammāvāyāmo?"
msgstr "And what is right effort?"

msgctxt "dn22:21.20"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"anuppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti "
"padahati;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts "
"the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise."

msgctxt "dn22:21.21"
msgid ""
"uppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati "
"vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati;"
msgstr ""
"They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so "
"that bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen are given up."

msgctxt "dn22:21.22"
msgid ""
"anuppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ uppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ "
"ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati;"
msgstr ""
"They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so "
"that skillful qualities arise."

msgctxt "dn22:21.23"
msgid ""
"uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya "
"bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ "
"paggaṇhāti padahati."
msgstr ""
"They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so "
"that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, "
"mature, and are completed by development."

msgctxt "dn22:21.24"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāvāyāmo. (6)"
msgstr "This is called right effort."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc126"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:21.25"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sammāsati?"
msgstr "And what is right mindfulness?"

msgctxt "dn22:21.26"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "dn22:21.27"
msgid ""
"vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing an aspect of feelings—keen, aware, and mindful, rid "
"of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "dn22:21.28"
msgid ""
"citte cittānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing an aspect of the mind—keen, aware, and mindful, rid "
"of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "dn22:21.29"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, "
"rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "dn22:21.30"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāsati. (7)"
msgstr "This is called right mindfulness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc127"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:21.31"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammāsamādhi?"
msgstr "And what is right immersion?"

msgctxt "dn22:21.32"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected."

msgctxt "dn22:21.33"
msgid ""
"Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ "
"avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter "
"and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of "
"immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without "
"placing the mind and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "dn22:21.34"
msgid ""
"Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati, sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena "
"paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti "
"tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"And with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third "
"absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, "
"personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘"
"Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’"

msgctxt "dn22:21.35"
msgid ""
"Sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ "
"atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, they "
"enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with "
"pure equanimity and mindfulness."

msgctxt "dn22:21.36"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāsamādhi."
msgstr "This is called right immersion."

msgctxt "dn22:21.37"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṃ. (8)"
msgstr ""
"This is called the noble truth of the practice that leads to the cessation "
"of suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.314"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc128"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:21.38"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā dhammesu "
"dhammānupassī viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of principles internally, "
"externally, and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "dn22:21.39"
msgid ""
"Samudayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing the principles as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish."

msgctxt "dn22:21.40"
msgid ""
"‘Atthi dhammā’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya "
"paṭissatimattāya anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"Or mindfulness is established that principles exist, to the extent necessary "
"for knowledge and mindfulness. They meditate independent, not grasping at "
"anything in the world."

msgctxt "dn22:21.41"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati catūsu "
"ariyasaccesu."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the four noble truths."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn22:21.42"
msgid "Saccapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn22:21.43"
msgid "Dhammānupassanā niṭṭhitā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs22"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc129"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:22.1"
msgid ""
"Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, ime cattāro satipaṭṭhāne evaṃ bhāveyya sattavassāni, "
"tassa dvinnaṃ phalānaṃ aññataraṃ phalaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ"
msgstr ""
"Anyone who develops these four kinds of mindfulness meditation in this way "
"for seven years can expect one of two results:"

msgctxt "dn22:22.2"
msgid "diṭṭheva dhamme aññā; sati vā upādisese anāgāmitā."
msgstr ""
"enlightenment in the present life, or if there’s something left over, non-"
"return."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc130"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:22.3"
msgid "Tiṭṭhantu, bhikkhave, sattavassāni."
msgstr "Let alone seven years,"

msgctxt "dn22:22.4"
msgid ""
"Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, ime cattāro satipaṭṭhāne evaṃ bhāveyya cha vassāni … "
"pe …"
msgstr ""
"anyone who develops these four kinds of mindfulness meditation in this way "
"for six years …"

msgctxt "dn22:22.5"
msgid "pañca vassāni …"
msgstr "five years …"

msgctxt "dn22:22.6"
msgid "cattāri vassāni …"
msgstr "four years …"

msgctxt "dn22:22.7"
msgid "tīṇi vassāni …"
msgstr "three years …"

msgctxt "dn22:22.8"
msgid "dve vassāni …"
msgstr "two years …"

msgctxt "dn22:22.9"
msgid "ekaṃ vassaṃ …"
msgstr "one year …"

msgctxt "dn22:22.10"
msgid "tiṭṭhatu, bhikkhave, ekaṃ vassaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:22.11"
msgid ""
"Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, ime cattāro satipaṭṭhāne evaṃ bhāveyya sattamāsāni, "
"tassa dvinnaṃ phalānaṃ aññataraṃ phalaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ"
msgstr "seven months …"

msgctxt "dn22:22.12"
msgid "diṭṭheva dhamme aññā; sati vā upādisese anāgāmitā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.315"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc131"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:22.13"
msgid "Tiṭṭhantu, bhikkhave, satta māsāni."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:22.14"
msgid ""
"Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, ime cattāro satipaṭṭhāne evaṃ bhāveyya cha māsāni … "
"pe …"
msgstr "six months …"

msgctxt "dn22:22.15"
msgid "pañca māsāni …"
msgstr "five months …"

msgctxt "dn22:22.16"
msgid "cattāri māsāni …"
msgstr "four months …"

msgctxt "dn22:22.17"
msgid "tīṇi māsāni …"
msgstr "three months …"

msgctxt "dn22:22.18"
msgid "dve māsāni …"
msgstr "two months …"

msgctxt "dn22:22.19"
msgid "ekaṃ māsaṃ …"
msgstr "one month …"

msgctxt "dn22:22.20"
msgid "aḍḍhamāsaṃ …"
msgstr "a fortnight …"

msgctxt "dn22:22.21"
msgid "tiṭṭhatu, bhikkhave, aḍḍhamāso."
msgstr "Let alone a fortnight,"

msgctxt "dn22:22.22"
msgid ""
"Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, ime cattāro satipaṭṭhāne evaṃ bhāveyya sattāhaṃ, "
"tassa dvinnaṃ phalānaṃ aññataraṃ phalaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ"
msgstr ""
"anyone who develops these four kinds of mindfulness meditation in this way "
"for seven days can expect one of two results:"

msgctxt "dn22:22.23"
msgid "diṭṭheva dhamme aññā; sati vā upādisese anāgāmitāti."
msgstr ""
"enlightenment in the present life, or if there’s something left over, non-"
"return."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc132"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:22.24"
msgid ""
"Ekāyano ayaṃ, bhikkhave, maggo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ "
"samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa "
"sacchikiriyāya yadidaṃ cattāro satipaṭṭhānāti."
msgstr ""
"‘The four kinds of mindfulness meditation are the path to convergence. They "
"are in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow and crying, to "
"make an end of pain and sadness, to complete the procedure, and to realize "
"extinguishment.’"

msgctxt "dn22:22.25"
msgid "Iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttan”ti."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc133"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:22.26"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "dn22:22.27"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn22:22.28"
msgid "Mahāsatipaṭṭhānasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
